  "culturalTip": "People in Korea order food for delivery over the phone quite frequently because it is incredibly convenient. Fried chicken is the most popular delivery food, but the word for \"fried chicken\" in Korean is just 치킨 [chi-kin], which is the English loanword \"chicken\" but written in Hangeul and pronounced with a Korean accent. The native Korean word 닭 [dak] is used to refer to chicken which is not fried.",
